In the bid to deter the spread of the pandemic Coronavirus, the University of Ilorin Sunday directed its returning international students to go for medical examination. The Director, Centre for international education, CIE, of the institution, Professor Felicia Olasheinde-Williams, gave the directive in a letter to the international students of the school. The letter a copy of which she was obtained by newsmen in Ilorin Sunday, said the directive became necessary to prevent the spread of Coronavirus on the campus. She said all retuning international students must proceed to the University clinic for medical examination “so as to deter the spread of the virus within and outside the campus.” “Note that this medical test is an important requirement for maintaining your studentship with the University. “As such,you are enjoined to adhere strictly to the directive immediately on your arrival,” Olasheinde-Williams stated. Covid-19, an outbreak of respiratory disease caused by a novel Coronavirus was first detected in China and has now spread to more than 100 locations around the world including the United states, Europe and Africa.